  "prompt": "When the Night King's White Walkers take children, do they become fully grown like those at end of the Game of Thrones episode \"Oathbreaker?\"",
  "response": "In \"Game of Thrones,\" when the Night King's White Walkers take children, they do not become fully grown adults like the ones seen at the end of the episode \"Oathbreaker.\" Instead, the process involves the children being transformed into White Walkers themselves. This transformation appears to maintain the physical characteristics of the child, but they gain the powers and abilities of a White Walker. \n\nThe specific scene in \"Oathbreaker\" shows the Night King raising the dead, and while it does suggest that he can create new White Walkers from children, the exact mechanics of this transformation and what happens to the children during the process are not fully explained in the series. The implication is that they retain some form of their original identity but are now aligned with the Night King's will.",
